Tasks - Description:
Mail<hr>0793189993<hr>Seen with TANS.

Naming convention : dl_City

CANNOT BE CREATED FROM EXCHANGEONLINE UI

To create the dynmaicDistributionGroup via Powershell :

Connect-ExchangeOnline

New-DynamicDistributionGroup -Name ''dl_Lausanne'' -RecipientContainer ''taurushq.com'' -RecipientFilter {RecipientType -eq “UserMailbox” -and City -eq ''Lausanne''}

 

Do not execute that command before validation.

To retrieve all the members from the ddl :

CONNECT-EXCHANGEONLINE

CONNECT-AZUREAD (OR GRAPH)

$users = Get-DynamicDistributionGroupMember -Identity ''dl_Lausanne).Name

foreach($user in $users){

Get-AzureADuser -ObjectID $user

}

Add the requester in the condition Alias -eq ''Johan'' for example

Do a test with the requester first. After validation, remove that optional condition.

Title: Perte de reseau si laptop non utilisé pendant 1h (200615)
Tasks - Description:
On a agréé de garder le ticket ouvert pour valider que ça a résolu le problème, ainsi il peut obsérver.  

Donc on regarde à nouveau le jeudi 18. ou vendredi 19. mai, soit pour clôturer ou pour poursuivre dans les recherches.<hr>https://daanberg.net/en/kennisbank/disable-energy-efficient-ethernet-in-windows/

 

Sur les deux cartes réseau du laptop (Ethernet et adapteur pour USB (donc pour la docking USB-C) J'ai désactivé:

Idle Power Saving
Energy Efficient Ethernet

Avec ça, ça ne devrait plus déconnecter la connexion réseau quand la machine n'est pas en utilisation mais activé.

 

En plus, j'ai changé les Power Settings pour faire en sorte que le laptop ne se met pas en veille quand c'est sur secteur.

 

 <hr>From networking - Getting disconnected from LAN and Internet after an hour or so - reboot resolves the issue - Super User

Devices getting disconnected after an hour is often a power management issue of the devices.

Make sure for all Network Cards, in Device Manager - Allow this device to turn OFF is disabled. In Advanced Power Management, make sure Network Cards are set for Maximum Performance (not Power Saving).

------

Make sure for all Network Cards, in Device Manager - Allow this device to turn OFF is disabled. In Advanced Power Management, make sure Network Cards are set for Maximum Performance (not Power Saving).

Dell driver updates are in order, they were recently installed (2.5.2023).  BIOS is up to date (spring of this year)

ipconfig / release renew

Title: VPN connection URGENT (196223)
Tasks - Description:
The issue is not with the VPN but with a change of password. As the user is working from home the change of password has not been updated.

The trick, when a user is working from home :

- Change the password 

- Ensure to be connected to the VPN

- Switch user

- Other user

- Use the new credential

- Enter into the session

The password update is done.
